HEADWORD: flooded
<hw>flooded</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>covered or overflowing
with water.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> afloat(predicate), awash(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>filled to overflowing as if with water; <as>as, a
desk flooded with applications</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> inundated, swamped.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flooder</ent>⟦br⟧
